post_text:
USD 271 School Day is 8am-3:30pm. We request that students do not arrive before 7:30am.

Arrival Assignments:

(A) North Door: Pre K, K, Kuhlmann, Kesler (Please travel from west to east and drop off at the sidewalk on the north end of the playground.)

(C) Main Door: Hohmann, Hemphill, 3rd, 4th Dryden, Dix (Use the circle drive and drop off just before you end the cross walk.)

(D) Cafeteria Door: Brown, Stamper-Voss, 6th, 7th (Enter off Hwy 24 and pull behind the high school, turn down Tiger Alley and drop off your children after the car in front of you has exited. One drop off at a time.)

If you have multiple children, please drop off at the youngest child's requested entry.

Together we can!

post_text:
Preschool and Kindergarten Meet Your Teacher Night

When: Tuesday, August 25th
Where: Stockton Grade School
Time: 4:00-6:30 PM - Come and go for a brief visit

We will be welcoming nearly 60 preschoolers and kindergartners to SGS this fall! We want our students and parents/caregivers to have the opportunity to visit the classroom, say hello to teachers, and practice arrival routines!

We request that only the preschool students and kindergarten students attend with the parent/caregiver during this time.

We will ask that everyone who enters the building wears a mask. We will practice taking a forehead no-touch temperature and the use of hand sanitizer.

Mrs. Hamel's and Mrs. William's students will enter at the north end, single door labeled A.
Mrs. Hazen's students will enter in the front, north end double doors, labeled B.

Please let us know if you have any questions.
We are so excited to welcome our youngest Tigers to USD 271!

Physical and Concussion forms are located on our school website: www.usd271.com, these are located under the "New Feed", you may turn in physicals and concussion forms to the High School or Grade School Offices.

post_text:
2020 USD #271 Summer Weight Room

USD #271 will be opening the weight room, starting on June 1, 2020. The weight room will be open to students in grades 6-12 for the 2020-2021 school year. Weight room hours and days: 6:00 am to 9:00 am, Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, and Friday.
We will be following the Governor’s and Rooks County Health Departments COVID-19 health guidance. We ask that students follow these rules:
DO NOT attend if they are not feeling well and/or have a temperature
Wash hands frequently
Cover Coughs
Mask may be worn (provided by the student)
Students will bring a personal water bottle (drinking fountains will be closed)
Utilize disinfectant (wipes, disinfectant bottles) before and after utilizing fitness equipment.
Maintain appropriate social distancing as directed by the state of Kansas and the Rooks County Health Department.

post_text: Kansas is amazing! Learning across Kansas!
shared_text:
Kansas State Department of Education
April 17 at 4:46 PM ·

We are excited to announce that Kansas teachers, students and parents just got a new partner in their continuous learning efforts.

Thanks to the support of Kansas Public Broadcasters, Kansas students will receive supplemental education content by way of a new television program produced by Kansas PBS stations and KSDE, and hosted by local teachers. The new program called Learning Across Kansas will begin airing the week of April 20.

Each 30-minute segment, individually produced for elementary, middle school and high school students, will feature grade-specific educational content delivered by our very own Kansas teachers who serve on KSDE’s Continuous Learning Task Force.

Teachers, students and parents/caregivers, tune in for short, fun and engaging lessons. Plus, you just might see one of your own teachers presenting!

Learn more by visiting, https://www.ksde.org/Agency/Fiscal-and-Administrative-Services/Communications-and-Recognition-Programs/Learning-Across-Kansas

post_text:
Solutions North Bank has put together a series of 5 lessons to teach students about money and banking. The first lesson launches today, Wednesday, April 8th. The lessons will be shared on social media and on our YouTube channel. Each lesson is short, approximately 5 minutes each, and also includes an activity sheet for them to complete afterward. The lessons are created for students up to a 5th grade level.

After completing a lesson, students will earn an “SNB Buck”. They will save their bucks and bring them into the bank at the completion of the series to buy a prize.

Their hope is that kids can easily learn more about banking and finances from home. Learning about healthy money habits at a young age is becoming even more important in today’s society. Thank you for supporting our students and families!

Here is the link to the first lesson:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EauiwR8aYw8



Activity Sheet:

https://drive.google.com/file/d/13fel_Xtn6YDpaOjOKBDDtZwfJhaxsSb9/view

post_text:
Our USD 271 posts are often directed toward our elementary students. We have found a resource we can share with our middle and high school students. Dr. Tim Elmore is an author and speaker. He is an expert on Generation Y and Generation Z. Tonight we are sharing an activity called Trains and Tracks (Structure). We hope you can engage your teen in this chat.

Think about a train moving along tracks. It would be easy to assume the tracks prevent the train from moving freely, but it’s just the opposite. The tracks give the train focus and direction. A train without tracks is just a disaster waiting to happen. You are just like this train. If you want to move forward you’ll need structures and systems to keep you on track and help you make progress. (Thank you Dr. Elmore and staff.)

post_text: Governor Kelly made an executive order today to close schools for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. All activities will be canceled. This will include Prom and Graduation as currently scheduled. The Continuous Learning Committee will be making recommendations for the District to use to create a Continuous Learning plan for USD 271. This plan should be able to be completed by March 30th. It is a priority of our School District to develop a plan that all students can continue to learn and Seniors can earn their High School diploma. All of the teaching staff will be utilized in this plan. We will continue to serve breakfast and lunch during this period on a grab and go basis for children 1-18 years of age free of charge. By the end of the week, our custodial staff will have the entire district disinfected.

post_text: Thank you to all Kansas teachers. A special thanks our amazing USD 271 teachers and staff! #BeTheOne271
shared_text:
Kansas State Department of Education
March 17 at 9:01 AM ·

The Continuous Learning Task Force worked throughout the night on a comprehensive plan for delivering education to students while school buildings remain closed. The task force anticipates having a draft of this plan finalized by the end of the day Wednesday, March 18.

We can’t emphasize enough that this is a herculean effort being led by our Kansas teachers. We thank this group - and every teacher in Kansas - for all they’re doing to ensure that learning continues for our students.

Please lend them your support, and trust that they are working to provide the very best opportunities for our students during this time of uncertainty.

EDIT March 17 4:25 p.m. - The list of educators on the Continuous Learning Task Force is available here: https://www.ksde.org/Home/Quick-Links/News-Room/commissioner-watson-convenes-continuous-learning-task-force-1

post_text: USD 271 continues to work closely with our state department of education (KSDE) and our health experts (KDHE). Based on the latest information, we will close school this week, March 16-20, and observe our Spring Break next week, March 23-27. There will be no school activities during this time. We will continue to communicate updates during these two weeks.

post_text: USD 271 is closely monitoring the COVID-19 virus. We receive daily updates from KSDE who is working closely with KDHE and CDC. We are “mitigating the risk” of COVID-19 by following the guidelines and recommendations from the state’s medical leadership. We are asking all parents to self-report any out of state or out of country travel to the school office where your child(ren) attends. The most common symptoms of COVID-19 are a fever and lower respiratory infection with cough. Students and staff may not attend school if they have not been fever free for 24 or more hours without the use of medication. We are under the direction of the Rooks County Health Department regarding school closure.

post_text:
Early Childhood Child Find!
USD 271 Stockton will offer early childhood opportunities for students ages three to five for the 2020-2021 school year. As we plan for the new school year, our child find is very important. Please pre-enroll by February 28, 2020.

Please contact Deb Carsten or Stacey Green at Stockton Grade School for pre-enrollment. 785-425-6120

You can also email your child’s information to Stacey Green at sgreen@usd271.com

Opportunities:
*We offer a three year old program, children must be potty-trained, and be 3 years of age by 8/31/20. Half-day sessions will be held for three year olds.
*We offer a four year old program for children who will be 4 years of age by 8/31/20. Half-day sessions will be held for four year olds.
*We offer full-day kindergarten for children who will be 5 years of age by 8/31/20.
Our three and four year old programs will also offer early childhood special education services.

post_text:
USD 271 Schools have seen an increase in student illnesses. We are monitoring these closely and continue to be attentive to our cleaning practices. As schools, parents, and kids we can "do the right thing" by practicing:
1) Good hygiene--wash hands!
2) Go home when you are sick.
3) Stay home until you are well (24 hours without fever and meds, not hacking/coughing all over others).
Thank you!

post_text: he National Honor Society is once again promoting the Pennies for Patients program at SHS. This program is sponsored by the Leukemia and Lymphoma Society. Their mission is to cure blood cancers and improve the lives of patients and their families. Donations to help with this cause can be placed in the container located in the SHS hallway or the link to our school's online giving page is https://events.lls.org/pages/mid/StocktonHighSchool-2020. This event will run through February 7.

Mrs. Kesler's Classroom Adventures
January 27 at 9:46 PM ·

Our Go2Science adventure is in Kenya! We are helping scientists decide if there is drinkable water under a school so they don’t have to haul water anymore. Today we made our own water filters and tested them with dirty water. So much fun! Go2Science
